	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>July 11th 5614</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Rev Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am sorry I could not<lb/> keep my promise to send you the rev<lb/> of the manuscript from <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The fact is I felt so warm and<lb/> fatigued there that I could not attend to<lb/> any thing and was actually glad to get<lb/> home as soon as possible.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed you will find the<lb/> <sic>ballance</sic> of the article.  I am not aware<lb/> whether or not I lost some of the intermed<lb/>iate pages&#44; you will be able to see <sic>wether</sic> the connection is there or not&#44; should a few<lb/> lines be wanting I trust to your good<lb/> taste and <sic>judgement</sic> to supply the<lb/> deficiency.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Trusting that you are<lb/> in the enjoyment of good health&#44; a bless&#45;<lb/>ing which I and mine thank God enjoy</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">yours most respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Solomon Jacobs</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Editor&#44; Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Pen</placeName>&#45;</p>
		</body>
